window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>They say it's hoes before bros. Too bad love never got the memo.</p> <p>Crystal knew that getting tangled up with Logan was a bad idea. Last year he broke her best friend’s heart. But with both her friends in love and Logan back to skate for the Blizzard, they were both misfits.</p> <p>Their relationship was never meant to be more than a secret fling.</p> <p>But secrets don’t stay buried forever.</p> <p>When one of Crystal’s art pieces is picked up by a prestigious curator, she has one shot to make a name for herself before graduation—but only if she can focus long enough to submit new work. Trouble is, her mind is tangled in guilt over Logan, fear of betraying her friends, and a relationship that’s no longer as hidden as she thought.</p> <p><i>Because now there’s a blurry photo of her on his arm. And an on-campus rumor mill.</i></p> <p>Crystal has everything to lose… But is Logan someone she can give up to protect it?</p> <p>One Click if you love:</p> <ul> <li>Forbidden Romance</li> <li>Secret Romance</li> <li>Tight knit girlfriends</li> <li>Slow burn</li> <li>Snarky banter</li> <li>Found Family</li> </ul> <p><i>Book #3 in Campus Confessions, a spin-off of the best-selling Canadian Played series. High sizzle, fade-to-black hockey romance.</i></p>"; 
